```mermaid
  graph TD;
      processMDFile-->inlineLocalReferences;
      inlineLocalReferences-->processMDFile
```

There was a curly brace error in the code of the bad example in 3.3 in the Korean translation. I have corrected this part.

// 나쁜 예
function someFunction() {
  // 코드 블록
}

↓ change

// 나쁜 예
function someFunction()
{
  // 코드 블록
}

In the main `README` description about dos and don'ts about curly braces positions. They are same leading to confusion

It is
```javascript
// Do
function someFunction() {
  // code block
}

// Avoid
function someFunction() {
  // code block
}
```

Should have been 

```javascript
// Do
function someFunction() {
  // code block
}

// Avoid
function someFunction() 
{
  // code block
}
```
